<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1506">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/139.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Vice Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-27">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>If Carranza complains that we appealed to Villa please explain to him
                                that we have acted in this case as we have in all others whether the
                                question arose in territory under his control or in territory under
                                Huerta. We have made representations to the local authorities first
                                    <pb facs="0972" n="856" xml:id="pg_856"/> in the hope of
                                securing immediate action and afterwards to the highest authorities.
                                Villa has consented to allow inspection of Benton’s body and
                                assuming that Carranza will approve of this we are arranging trip
                                but would like specific approval from Carranza and assurance of
                                protection of party which will include British Consul. We still hope
                                that body will be delivered to widow. Assure Carranza that we
                                appreciate the efforts he has made to protect life and property of
                                foreigners.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>